text:
Flushing Meadow Park (Queens): Three views across the salt meadows of the lower end of the park, marking the site where the amusement area of the New York World's Fair of 1939-40 was later erected.

View 1 is northeastward from about 75th Avenue and 113th Place; view 2 is southeastward; view 3 is east toward several Jamaica cemeteries.
